@granthenke : Sorry for the delay. Just a couple of minor comments.
1. log.cleaner.delete.retention.ms doesn't have to match log.retention. If a consumer has never seen any existing message for a key, it's ok for the consumer not to see the tombstone. It's only when a consumer has seen an existing message and the key is deleted, we expect the consumer to read the tombstone within some window. The current default of 1 day seems long enough. So, I recommend that we keep the current default.
2. Is 128 MiB a typo? Should it be 128MB?

@rhauch Got it, I feel this is a good motivation to dynamically change partitioning behaviors, and will also help in translating the higher-level DSL's join operations to co-partition the joining streams / tables. 

What I mean by is that currently users need to use `map` in order to co-partition the joining streams on the same key type, while in the future this could be abstracted from them, and as a result Kafka Streams will do the re-partitioning automatically that generates intermediate Kafka streams that are not exposed to users.

Regarding the proposed PR, its API change makes sense to me as well. Could you rebase this PR for a final review? If you do not have time I can help the rebasing.

